# Environment Variables Template for Vercel

## Backend Environment Variables

```bash
# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/github-automation?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# Authentication
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production

# GitHub
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# AI Service
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key

# Frontend URL (will be set after frontend deployment)
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend.vercel.app

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# Port (Vercel will override this)
PORT=3001
```

## Frontend Environment Variables

```bash
# Backend API URL (will be set after backend deployment)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend.vercel.app
```

## How to Set in Vercel Dashboard

1. Go to your project in Vercel
2. Click on "Settings"
3. Click on "Environment Variables"
4. Add each variable:
   - Name: Variable name (e.g., `MONGODB_URI`)
   - Value: Variable value
   - Environment: Production (and optionally Preview/Development)
5. Click "Save"

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env` files to Git
- Use different values for development and production
- Rotate secrets regularly
- Use MongoDB Atlas for production (not local MongoDB)
- Enable IP whitelisting in MongoDB Atlas
- Use strong JWT secrets (at least 32 characters)

## Getting Required API Keys

### MongoDB Atlas
1. Go to https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
2. Sign up and create a free cluster
3. Create a database user
4. Get connection string from "Connect" button

### GitHub Token
1. Go to GitHub Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens
2. Generate new token (classic)
3. Select scopes: `repo`, `workflow`, `read:user`

### Gemini API Key
1. Go to https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
2. Create API key
3. Copy the key
